  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Core Responsibility (CORE) coalition grant 2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CORE is currently leading an NGO coalition campaign for a transparency in supply chains clause to be included in the Modern Slavery Bill. If passed, this will require large companies operating in the UK to report on what they are doing to identify and address slavery in their international supply chains. This will lead into work on the transposition into UK law of the EU directive on non -financial reporting, with the aim of creating a requirement for all large UK companies (including non -listed companies) to report on social, environmental, labour and human rights issues throughout their supply chains. (see attached application for further details)</narrative>
  </description>
